  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      to investigate the function of the autonomic nervous system in children with with post
      traumatic brain injury and children with cerebral palsy through an analysis of heart rate
      variability (HRV) occurring with walking performance.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      40 children with brain damage (20 with post TBI and 20 with CP)and 40 typically developed
      children will be participate in this study. ECG signals during rest and walking (for 6 minute
      and during step climbing) will be recorded.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
